# How to Run EasyCart 2.1 Locally

This guide explains how to start the development environment for both the **Spring Boot Backend** and the **Vanilla JS Frontend**.

## 🚀 Quick Start Commands

Open two separate terminals in your project root:

### Terminal 1: The Backend (Spring Boot)
```powershell
cd backend
mvn spring-boot:run
```
*Wait for the log: `Started EasyCartSmeApplication in ... seconds`*

### Terminal 2: The Frontend (Static Server)
```powershell
cd frontend
npx -y http-server -p 3000
```
*Your website will be live at `http://localhost:3000`*

